  "text": "The Kubernetes CRD validation schema to OpenAPI v3 publishing chain traces through the following components:\n\n1. **CRD Validation Spec Definition** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/types.go)\n   - CustomResourceValidation struct (and v1 variant in v1/types.go) contains the OpenAPIV3Schema field\n   - This field holds a JSONSchemaProps object representing the validation schema for a CustomResourceDefinition\n\n2. **Structural Schema Extraction** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/convert.go)\n   - NewStructural() function converts JSONSchemaProps from CRD validation into a Structural schema\n   - The Structural schema is an internal representation that normalizes the OpenAPI v3 schema\n   - Recursively processes nested properties, items, and validation rules\n\n3. **OpenAPI Schema Conversion** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/kubeopenapi.go)\n   - ToKubeOpenAPI() method on Structural converts the structural schema to spec.Schema (kube-openapi format)\n   - Handles conversion of properties, items, additional properties, generic metadata, and Kubernetes-specific extensions\n   - Preserves x-kubernetes-* vendor extensions like x-kubernetes-preserv-unknown-fields, x-kubernetes-list-type, etc.\n\n4. **OpenAPI Builder** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go)\n   - generateBuilder() extracts the validation schema for a specific CRD version and converts it to Structural schema using NewStructural()\n   - BuildOpenAPIV3() calls generateBuilder() and then builder3.BuildOpenAPISpecFromRoutes() to generate the final OpenAPI v3 specification\n   - Constructs RESTful routes for CRUD operations and marshals them into OpenAPI v3 spec\n\n5. **OpenAPI v3 Controller** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go)\n   - Controller watches CustomResourceDefinitions for changes\n   - buildV3Spec() calls builder.BuildOpenAPIV3() to generate OpenAPI v3 spec for each CRD version\n   - updateGroupVersion() merges specs from multiple CRDs in the same group/version and calls openAPIV3Service.UpdateGroupVersion()\n   - Updates are persisted in specsByGVandName map for in-memory storage\n\n6. **OpenAPI Service Handler** (vendor/k8s.io/kube-openapi/pkg/handler3/handler.go)\n   - OpenAPIService manages the OpenAPI v3 specifications for all group/versions\n   - UpdateGroupVersion() stores or updates the spec for a group/version\n   - Maintains mapping of GroupVersion to OpenAPI spec objects\n\n7. **API Server Endpoint Publication** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/openapi.go)\n   - InstallV3() registers the /openapi/v3 endpoint with the API server\n   - Calls openAPIVersionedService.RegisterOpenAPIV3VersionedService(\"/openapi/v3\", mux)\n   - Handler serves OpenAPI v3 specifications for all APIs including CRDs via HTTP\n\nThe complete flow: CRD CustomResourceValidation → JSONSchemaProps → NewStructural (conversion) → ToKubeOpenAPI (conversion to spec.Schema) → BuildOpenAPIV3 (builder wraps in routes) → buildV3Spec (controller calls builder) → UpdateGroupVersion (publishes to service) → /openapi/v3 HTTP endpoint (clients access via API server)"
